# Testing Conventions

## Structural Convention Tests

New structural rules added to agent/skill templates MUST have corresponding static detection tests in `tests/static/`.

## RED-First Strategy

When adding new conventions:
1. Write failing tests first (RED phase)
2. Implement in parallel worktrees
3. Verify all tests pass (GREEN)

## Parameterized Batch Assertions

Use `pytest.mark.parametrize` to assert conventions across all applicable files:

- Agent hardening tests → parametrize over ALL_AGENTS / REVIEW_AGENTS lists
- Skill lint checks → parametrize over all SKILL.md paths
- Keep agent/file lists at module top for easy maintenance

## Test File Organization

- `tests/static/` — structural/lint checks (no runtime, fast)
- `tests/static/lint_skills.py` — SKILL.md structural checks
- `tests/static/test_agent_hardening.py` — agent template checks
- `tests/static/anchor_keywords.yaml` — required section anchors per skill/agent
